body:
The following code is expected to compile without errors.

```rust
pub trait Foo {}
pub trait Bar<T>: Foo {}

pub trait Foo2 {}
pub trait Bar2<T>: Foo2 {}


impl<T> Foo2 for T where T: Foo {}
impl<U, T> Bar2<U> for T where T: Bar<U> {}

impl<T> Foo2 for Option<T> where T: Foo2 {}
impl<U, T> Bar2<U> for Option<T> where T: Bar2<U> {}
```

However possible conflict implementation in upstream crates is detected.

Rewriting 2nd impl as:
```rust
impl<U, T> Bar2<U> for T where T: Bar<U> + Foo {}
```
i.e. adding `Foo` bound,
solves the issue. Which should not be required as `Foo` is supertrait of `Bar`.

